  "prompt": "How much time does a waiter spend in taking orders?",
  "response": "The amount of time a waiter spends taking orders can vary based on several factors, including the type of restaurant, the complexity of the menu, the number of tables they are serving, and the individual waiter's efficiency. \n\nOn average, a waiter might spend anywhere from a few minutes to 10-15 minutes per table when taking orders. This includes greeting the customers, explaining the menu, answering questions, and processing the order. During busy periods, this time can be shorter as waiters may prioritize efficiency. In a fine dining setting where more detailed explanations and personal interactions are expected, it may take longer.\n\nOverall, in a typical restaurant shift, a waiter could spend several hours cumulatively taking orders throughout the day.",
